OL,3,CTrapped between bombs and crackdowns:
OL,4,CIranians wrestle with decision to flee
OL,6,F"The journey is terrifying, especially
OL,7,Ffor older people. You wait in the heat
OL,8,Ffor five or six hours just to cross
OL,9,Fthe border. It's not something I'd
OL,10,Frecommend to anyone with health issues
OL,11,For kids."
OL,13,FBut not everyone is leaving, or able
OL,14,Fto.
OL,16,F"This is my home," says Homa, who is
OL,17,F54. "My daughter is in a wheelchair. I
OL,18,Fcan't travel a long distance like that
OL,19,Fwith her. And even if I could ` where
OL,20,Fwould we go?"
